description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for Band 6 Senior Staff nurse vacancies within the Emergency Unit at Cardiff and Vale UHB.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiff and Vale UHBs Emergency Unit assesses over 150,000 patients a year. The unit provides care for acutely ill or injured patients of all ages. As well as a large resuscitation and majors trolley area, the unit also has a nurse led minor injuries service and a dedicated peadiatric area. Cardiff and Vale UHB are also becoming a Major Trauma Centre in April 2020. This exciting development will allow staff to be exposed to all types of major trauma and training associated with this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are welcomed from qualified Level 1 Registered Nurses who have significant experience within Emergency Medicine and can demonstrate substantial knowledge within this field of expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be identified as a clinical expert within Emergency Nursing and will be expected mange the flow within specific areas of the Emergency Unit, providing effective leadership and management of the nursing team in an environment which is complex and pressurised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will require excellent communication and clinical skills, significant evidence of CPD and show passion and enthusiasm for working in Emergency Medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a wonderful career opportunity to further enhance clinical skills relating to emergency medicine and major trauma. If you welcome change, innovation in a challenging but rewarding environment we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jacqui Westmoreland or Cath Morris&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;02920743416&lt;/p&gt;
